bcl:definition.bcl:text:
federal Act means the Agricultural Products Marketing Act (Canada), the
  Farm Products Agencies Act (Canada) or the Canadian Dairy Commission Act (Canada),
or any of them, as the case may be;

marketing includes producing, packing, buying, selling, storing,
shipping for sale, offering for sale or storage, and in respect of a natural product
includes its transportation in any manner by any person;

natural product means a product of agriculture or of the sea, lake or
river and an article of food or drink wholly or partly manufactured or derived from such
product;

regulated product means a natural product the regulation of the
marketing of which is provided for in a scheme approved or established under this
Act;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
to require full information relating to the marketing of a regulated product
            from all persons engaged in marketing activities, to require periodic returns to be made
            by those persons and to inspect the books and premises of those persons;

to make orders and rules considered by the marketing board or commission
            necessary or advisable to promote, control and regulate effectively the marketing of a
            regulated product, and to amend or revoke them;

to purchase a regulated product in relation to which it may exercise its powers
            and package, process, store, ship, insure, export, sell or otherwise dispose of the
            product purchased by it;

to initiate, support or conduct programs for promoting, stimulating, increasing
          and improving the economic position of persons engaged in the marketing of that natural
          product;

stop and detain a vehicle or other form of conveyance that contains or that the
            Provincial board, marketing board, commission or person has reason to believe contains,
            a regulated product;

take a sample of a natural product or a thing used in relation to the production
          of a natural product, submit a sample to a specified person or permit a specified person
          to take a sample;

the approval of a scheme for the regulation of the marketing of a natural
            product for which the approval of the Lieutenant Governor in Council is necessary for a
            purpose of the federal Act;

the submission of a scheme for the regulation of the marketing of a natural
            product to a plebiscite in the area of British Columbia covered by the
            scheme;

the termination and annulment of an approval given or scheme authorized by the
            Lieutenant Governor in Council under this Act and the disposition of the assets of a
            marketing board if its appointment or authority is annulled;
